      <h2 id="mission">Mission</h2>
      <p>ZION OASIS is an initiative built around a consciousness-based blockchain economy that prioritizes humanitarian impact, ethical participation, and community sovereignty. The aim is to channel value to education, healthcare, and welfare projects while aligning incentives for spiritual growth.</p>

      <h2 id="pillars">Pillars</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Humanitarian Fund</strong> — a transparent allocation (testnet placeholder) dedicated to children and vulnerable communities.</li>
        <li><strong>Consciousness Mining</strong> — miners earn multipliers (1×–15×) based on development levels (research-in-progress on testnet).</li>
        <li><strong>DAO Governance</strong> — a long-term transition of decision power to the community (20-year vision).</li>
        <li><strong>Sustainability</strong> — incentives for responsible energy usage and community-oriented infrastructure.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="architecture">Architecture (Overview)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Node & P2P</strong> — secure networking, block propagation, state management.</li>
        <li><strong>Consensus & Mining</strong> — 2-minute blocks, multi-algorithm mining (RandomX, Autolykos v2, Cosmic Harmony — subject to change on testnet).</li>
        <li><strong>Pools</strong> — optional aggregation via Stratum-like interfaces.</li>
        <li><strong>Wallet</strong> — keys, transactions, participation in governance (future phases).</li>
        <li><strong>Explorers & APIs</strong> — transparency, tooling, and developer access.</li>
        <li><strong>Bridges</strong> — future integrations for AI compute and cross-domain collaborations (concept under exploration).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="programs">Programs</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Education</strong> — learning resources, scholarships, and community workshops.</li>
        <li><strong>Healthcare</strong> — basic medical support and prevention campaigns.</li>
        <li><strong>Community</strong> — local projects, micro-grants, food and shelter initiatives.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="participation">Participation</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Run a node and help secure the network (<a href="setup.html">Setup Guide</a>).</li>
        <li>Contribute code, report issues, or improve docs.</li>
        <li>Propose humanitarian projects and accountability measures.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="roadmap">Roadmap (TestNet)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Stabilize testnet protocols and metrics.</li>
        <li>Publish draft governance guidelines and feedback loops.</li>
        <li>Prototype funding flows and transparency dashboards.</li>
        <li>Iterate with community on eligibility and impact criteria.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="note">All specifics are subject to change during TestNet. Watch the repository for updates and release notes.</div>
